This paper proposes a method for training a Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) for video generation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the computational challenges of training large models, which could potentially fall under the multimedia (cs.MM), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories.
